16 Chittenden Place, west side, at the extremitv of W. 185th Street, showing an overhanging structure built by an architect for self occupancy. An engraving of same by Vercon Ho e Bailey apoeared in the New York Sun of May 1934. The photogranhers vantage point is Riwerside Drive, which appears in the foreground and he is viewing northeastward.
June 23, 1934.
P.L. Sperr
A similar view from Dr. Chas. V. Paterno's estate, the adjoining property, and upon which is being constructed,the distinctive Castle Village. Note debris from same in the foreground. The photographer is viewing northwestward from atop the bluff, Cabrini Blvd. (formerly Northern Avenue).
October,21, 1938
George D. Chinn
No Reproductions
